context: The word 'jõuavad' is the third person plural present indicative form of the Estonian verb 'jõuda', which means 'to arrive', 'to reach', 'to come', or 'to get to'. It describes when people (or subjects) are arriving somewhere in the present moment. The root 'jõu-' relates to power/strength, suggesting the action of successfully reaching a destination through one's own strength or effort.
